-- ── 1. Anti-Stress Face Mask ──────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is the Mesoestetic Anti-Stress Face Mask right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin feels red, tight or reactive after Dermapen, chemical peels or other in-clinic treatments</li><li>You have <strong>sensitive or rosacea-prone skin</strong> that flares with many products</li><li>Your skin feels overwhelmed after a long week — stressed, dull and uncomfortable</li><li>You want a weekly treatment that resets your barrier and calms visible inflammation</li><li>You have been recommended this by Dr. Bangalee as part of your post-procedure home care</li></ul><h3>How the Anti-Stress Face Mask works — the science</h3><p>Stressed and post-procedure skin has two urgent needs: inflammation must be calmed and the barrier must be rebuilt. Most masks address one or the other. The <strong>Anti-Stress Face Mask addresses both simultaneously.</strong></p><p><strong>Centella Asiatica</strong> — the most clinically validated wound-healing botanical available — activates the skin's own repair response, stimulating collagen synthesis and accelerating barrier recovery. <strong>Allantoin</strong> suppresses the inflammatory cascade at the cellular level, reducing redness and discomfort within minutes of application. <strong>Chamomile extract</strong> provides complementary anti-inflammatory action through a different pathway, ensuring the calming effect is both immediate and sustained. <strong>Hyaluronic acid</strong> simultaneously replenishes the moisture that inflammation and procedure-related barrier compromise strips from the skin.</p><p>The result is a product that does not simply feel soothing — it measurably reduces redness, accelerates barrier recovery, and leaves the skin genuinely calmer, not just temporarily comfortable.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>During application:</strong> Immediate cooling and soothing sensation — redness and tightness begin to ease within minutes. <strong>After first use:</strong> Skin visibly calmer, softer and more comfortable. Post-procedure redness reduced. <strong>Week 1–2 of regular use:</strong> Reactive episodes become less frequent and less intense. Skin feels more resilient to daily stressors. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Sustained improvement in baseline skin comfort and reduction in reactive sensitivity over time.</p><h3>How to use the Anti-Stress Face Mask</h3><ol><li>Apply a generous, even layer to clean, dry skin — avoiding the eye area</li><li>Leave on for <strong>15–20 minutes</strong></li><li>Rinse off with cool water and pat dry gently — do not rub</li><li>Follow with your regular moisturiser, or apply on its own immediately after in-clinic procedures</li><li>Use <strong>1–2 times per week</strong> as a restorative treatment — or more frequently post-procedure as directed by Dr. Bangalee</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Centella Asiatica</td><td>Clinically proven wound-healing botanical — activates barrier repair, stimulates collagen, reduces post-procedure recovery time</td></tr><tr><td>Allantoin</td><td>Suppresses the inflammatory cascade at the cellular level — reduces redness and skin discomfort on contact</td></tr><tr><td>Chamomile Extract</td><td>Natural anti-inflammatory that calms stressed and sensitised skin through a complementary pathway to allantoin</td></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Binds water in the skin to restore the hydration depleted by inflammation, procedures and barrier compromise</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>After any ablative procedure — Dermapen, chemical peel, laser — the skin enters a temporary state of barrier compromise and heightened reactivity. The Anti-Stress Face Mask is in the post-procedure kit I recommend to virtually every patient for exactly this phase. It shortens the reactive period, reduces visible redness and gives patients the confidence to continue their treatment protocols without the discomfort that sometimes makes them stop. I use it weekly myself.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I used this the evening after my Dermapen and my skin was so much calmer than after previous sessions. The redness was gone by the next morning instead of lasting three days.</td><td>I have rosacea and finding a mask I can actually use is nearly impossible. This one doesn't flare me at all — it actually makes the redness better. I use it twice a week now.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee sent me home with this after my peel. I didn't expect much but it genuinely made the recovery faster. My skin felt like itself again within two days instead of a week.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use the Anti-Stress Face Mask immediately after a Dermapen treatment?</td><td>Yes — it is specifically designed for this purpose. Apply it on the evening after your Dermapen session as directed by Dr. Bangalee. The centella and allantoin complex begins calming post-needling inflammation immediately and supports barrier recovery overnight.</td></tr><tr><td>How often should I use it when I'm not recovering from a procedure?</td><td>1–2 times per week as a restorative maintenance treatment. This frequency keeps reactive skin calmer on an ongoing basis and provides a regular barrier-repairing dose of centella and hyaluronic acid even when no procedure has been performed.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it suitable for rosacea-prone skin?</td><td>Yes — the anti-inflammatory actives (centella, allantoin, chamomile) are specifically beneficial for rosacea-prone skin. The formula contains no alcohol, fragrance irritants or harsh actives that typically flare rosacea. Many patients with rosacea find it one of the few masks they can use without a reaction.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it during pregnancy?</td><td>The formula does not contain retinoids, high-dose salicylic acid or other actives restricted during pregnancy. The botanical ingredients (centella, chamomile) are generally considered safe topically. Confirm with your healthcare provider as a precaution, as individual circumstances vary.</td></tr><tr><td>What is the difference between this and Melan Recovery?</td><td>Anti-Stress Face Mask is a rinse-off treatment applied for 15–20 minutes — an intensive reset dose used 1–2 times per week. Melan Recovery is a leave-on daily balm used throughout the depigmentation protocol specifically to manage ongoing sensitivity. They serve different roles and can be used together during intensive treatment phases.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-anti-stress-face-mask';


-- ── 2. Aox Ferulic ────────────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Aox Ferulic right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin looks dull, uneven or prematurely aged despite a good skincare routine</li><li>You are exposed to sun, pollution or environmental stressors daily — which is everyone in Durban</li><li>You want to <strong>protect your collagen</strong> and prevent the damage that causes fine lines over time</li><li>You are in your 30s or 40s and beginning to see the first signs of skin quality decline</li><li>You are already using retinol or prescription actives and want a morning product to complement them</li><li>Dr. Bangalee has recommended an antioxidant serum as part of your anti-ageing protocol</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Aox Ferulic works — the science</h3><p>Every day your skin is bombarded by <strong>free radicals</strong> — unstable molecules generated by UV radiation, pollution and environmental stress. Free radicals break down collagen, trigger melanin overproduction and accelerate every visible sign of skin ageing. An antioxidant serum is the only topical product that neutralises this damage before it occurs.</p><p><strong>Vitamin C (ascorbic acid)</strong> is the most clinically proven antioxidant for the skin — it neutralises free radicals, directly stimulates collagen synthesis, and inhibits the melanin production triggered by UV exposure. The challenge has always been stability: pure Vitamin C oxidises rapidly on contact with air and light, losing its effectiveness before it can work. <strong>Ferulic acid</strong> solves this entirely — it stabilises both Vitamin C and Vitamin E at the molecular level, extending their active life on the skin and making the combination <strong>8x more effective</strong> than Vitamin C alone.</p><p>The exclusive <strong>Protech-Cell Complex</strong> adds a further layer of cellular defence — reinforcing the skin's own antioxidant enzyme systems so the protection is not only external but internal. The result is a morning serum that genuinely defends the skin against the damage that drives ageing, rather than simply treating the visible signs after they appear.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Improved radiance and brightness — skin looks fresher and more alive in the morning. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Skin tone becomes more even; dark spots fade slightly; skin feels firmer. <strong>Month 3+:</strong> Measurable improvement in fine lines, skin texture and overall skin quality. Collagen protection compounds with every day of consistent use. <strong>Long-term:</strong> The most significant benefit of Aox Ferulic is what you don't see — the premature ageing that didn't happen.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Aox Ferulic</h3><ol><li>Apply 3–4 drops to clean, dry skin each <strong>morning</strong> before moisturiser and SPF</li><li>Gently press into the face and neck — do not rub aggressively</li><li>Allow to absorb fully (1–2 minutes) before applying your next product</li><li>Follow with <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</strong> or your preferred SPF — SPF is mandatory</li><li>In the evening, use <strong>HA Densimatrix</strong> to pair day protection with overnight volumising</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Vitamin C (Ascorbic Acid)</td><td>Neutralises free radicals, stimulates collagen synthesis, brightens the complexion and inhibits UV-triggered melanin production</td></tr><tr><td>Ferulic Acid</td><td>Stabilises Vitamin C and Vitamin E — extends their active life on skin and amplifies their combined effectiveness 8-fold</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin E</td><td>Nourishes the skin, amplifies antioxidant protection and reinforces the skin barrier against environmental stressors</td></tr><tr><td>Protech-Cell Complex</td><td>Mesoestetic's exclusive cellular protection technology — activates the skin's own antioxidant enzyme systems for defence from within</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Aox Ferulic is the first serum I reach for in any anti-ageing protocol. My patients in Durban are exposed to some of the highest UV indices in South Africa year-round — the oxidative damage accumulates silently for years before patients see it. Starting a stabilised Vitamin C and ferulic acid serum in your 30s is one of the highest-return investments you can make in your skin's future. It is also the product I pair with every retinol protocol I prescribe — they work on different mechanisms and compound each other's results significantly.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>My skin looks genuinely different in the morning now. There's a glow I didn't have before and my SPF goes on more smoothly over it. I've been using it for three months and I'm not stopping.</td><td>I was sceptical about paying this much for a serum. After six weeks I could actually see the difference in my skin texture and the small lines around my eyes were less obvious. Worth every rand.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee recommended this alongside my retinol programme. My skin is brighter than it's been in years and the combination seems to work much better than either product on its own.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use Aox Ferulic with retinol?</td><td>Yes — use Aox Ferulic in the morning and your retinol in the evening. They are complementary, not competing. The antioxidant serum protects against daytime damage while retinoids drive overnight cellular renewal. Do not layer them at the same time, as pH requirements differ.</td></tr><tr><td>Why does Vitamin C need ferulic acid?</td><td>Pure Vitamin C oxidises rapidly when exposed to air and light — it can become ineffective within hours of opening. Ferulic acid stabilises the molecule at the chemical level, extending its active life and increasing its effectiveness by a factor of 8. A Vitamin C serum without ferulic acid is significantly less effective than one with it.</td></tr><tr><td>Should I use it in the morning or at night?</td><td>Morning is most effective. Its primary purpose is to neutralise free radicals generated by UV radiation and pollution during the day. Applied before SPF, it creates a two-layer defence system that is dramatically more protective than SPF alone. Applying it at night provides some benefit but misses its most important window.</td></tr><tr><td>How long before I see visible results?</td><td>Most patients notice improved radiance within 1–2 weeks. Significant improvements in skin tone, fine lines and firmness are typically visible after 2–3 months of consistent daily use. Antioxidant serums are a long-game investment — the greatest benefit is the collagen damage that doesn't accumulate.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it suitable for darker skin tones?</td><td>Yes — Vitamin C is safe and effective across all skin tones and is particularly valuable for melanin-rich skin as it fades post-inflammatory marks and evens tone without the risk of depigmentation from more aggressive treatments. It is fully compatible with the Melan Tran3x pigmentation protocol.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-aox-ferulic';


-- ── 3. Fast Skin Repair ───────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Fast Skin Repair right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have just had — or are planning — a <strong>Dermapen, chemical peel, laser</strong> or other ablative procedure at Star Aesthetic Centre</li><li>Your skin is visibly red, tender or compromised after a procedure and you want it to recover faster</li><li>Dr. Bangalee has included this in your post-procedure home care kit</li><li>Your skin barrier is chronically disrupted — red, dry and reactive regardless of treatment</li><li>You want to shorten recovery downtime and get back to your normal routine sooner</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Fast Skin Repair works — the science</h3><p>After any ablative procedure, the skin enters a structured healing cascade. The first 48 hours are inflammatory — the skin is red, warm and reactive as the immune system responds. Days 3–7 involve active tissue repair and barrier rebuilding. <strong>Fast Skin Repair is formulated to support both phases simultaneously</strong>, compressing the timeline without interfering with the biological process.</p><p><strong>Growth factors</strong> — the signal proteins that orchestrate cellular repair — activate fibroblasts to produce new collagen and elastin, directly accelerating the tissue renewal that post-procedure skin requires. <strong>Panthenol (Vitamin B5)</strong> is among the most evidence-backed wound-healing actives available topically: it increases fibroblast proliferation, accelerates re-epithelialisation and provides deep humectant action that keeps the healing tissue adequately hydrated. <strong>Centella Asiatica</strong> — already proven in surgical wound care — promotes collagen synthesis and vascular remodelling. Together, these actives work on the biological mechanisms of healing rather than simply masking redness with anti-inflammatory suppression.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Hours 1–24 post-procedure:</strong> Significant reduction in the heat and tightness of post-procedure inflammation — skin feels cushioned and soothed rather than raw. <strong>Days 2–3:</strong> Redness fades faster than without treatment. Barrier function begins to return. <strong>Days 4–7:</strong> Skin surface stabilises — peeling (if present) is minimised; healing tissue feels comfortable. <strong>Week 2:</strong> Skin looks and behaves normally — back to regular protocol sooner than expected.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Fast Skin Repair</h3><ol><li>Apply immediately after your in-clinic procedure as directed by Dr. Bangalee — or from the same evening</li><li>Apply a generous layer and press gently into skin — do not massage or rub</li><li>Reapply <strong>2–3 times per day</strong> during the acute recovery phase (days 1–5)</li><li>Reduce frequency as the skin normalises — transition to once daily, then back to your regular moisturiser</li><li>Avoid active skincare (retinols, AHAs, Vitamin C) until Dr. Bangalee clears you to resume</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Growth Factors</td><td>Signal proteins that activate fibroblasts to produce new collagen and elastin — directly accelerate tissue repair after procedures</td></tr><tr><td>Panthenol (Vitamin B5)</td><td>Increases fibroblast proliferation, accelerates re-epithelialisation and provides deep wound-healing hydration</td></tr><tr><td>Centella Asiatica</td><td>Stimulates collagen synthesis and vascular remodelling — proven in surgical wound care and post-procedure recovery</td></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Maintains optimal moisture levels in healing tissue — dehydrated wounds heal more slowly and scar more easily</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin E</td><td>Antioxidant protection against the oxidative stress that slows healing and contributes to post-procedure discolouration</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Fast Skin Repair is in every post-procedure kit I send home. The difference in recovery between patients who use it correctly and those who don't is visible at the two-day follow-up — it genuinely compresses the inflammatory phase. I also recommend it to patients with chronically disrupted barriers who have never had a procedure: if your skin is in a perpetual state of low-grade reactivity, this cream resets it faster than any standard moisturiser will.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>After my last Dermapen without this cream, I was red for almost a week. This time Dr. Bangalee gave me Fast Skin Repair and I was fine in two days. The difference was unbelievable.</td><td>I used this after my chemical peel and the recovery was so much faster than before. Barely any peeling and the redness was gone by day three instead of day eight.</td><td>My skin barrier was completely wrecked — tight, red and reactive all the time. This cream was the first thing that actually made a lasting difference in how comfortable my skin feels day to day.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>How soon after my Dermapen should I start using Fast Skin Repair?</td><td>Apply it on the same evening as your Dermapen procedure. Dr. Bangalee will apply the first layer in-clinic immediately post-treatment. Your home application continues from that evening — the sooner you begin, the faster the inflammatory phase resolves.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I wear makeup during recovery?</td><td>Avoid makeup for the first 48–72 hours after any ablative procedure. The skin barrier is temporarily compromised and the risk of irritation or infection from cosmetic ingredients is elevated. Once active healing is complete and redness has settled, a mineral-based concealer is generally safer than liquid foundation. Confirm timing with Dr. Bangalee.</td></tr><tr><td>How long does recovery typically take when using Fast Skin Repair?</td><td>For a light chemical peel, most patients are comfortable within 3–5 days. Medium-depth peels typically require 7–10 days of active recovery. Dermapen recovery is generally 3–5 days. Fast Skin Repair compresses these timelines by supporting the biological healing process rather than simply masking symptoms.</td></tr><tr><td>Does Fast Skin Repair contain steroids or cortisone?</td><td>No — it contains no steroids or cortisone. Its calming effects come from growth factors, centella asiatica and panthenol, which support the skin's own healing process. This makes it safe for extended post-procedure use without the risks associated with topical steroids such as skin thinning or rebound inflammation.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it only for post-procedure skin or can I use it for general dryness?</td><td>While its primary purpose is post-procedure recovery, it is excellent for any period when the barrier is significantly compromised — severe dryness, extreme weather exposure, eczema flares or other disrupted-barrier situations. Outside of these contexts, most patients are better served by Hydracream Fusion as their daily moisturiser.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-fast-skin-repair';


-- ── 4. Melan Recovery ─────────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Melan Recovery right for you?</h3><ul><li>You are on the <strong>Melan Tran3x or Cosmelan depigmentation protocol</strong> prescribed by Dr. Bangalee</li><li>Your skin is red, sensitised or uncomfortable after a chemical peel or pigmentation treatment</li><li>You need a daily moisturiser during active treatment that soothes without interfering with depigmenting actives</li><li>Your skin tends to become reactive during intensive protocols and you need support to continue comfortably</li><li>Dr. Bangalee has recommended this as part of your prescribed depigmentation home care</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Melan Recovery works — the science</h3><p>Depigmentation treatments work by deliberately suppressing melanin production — a process that the skin often experiences as stress, particularly in the first weeks of an intensive protocol. Melan Recovery is formulated to provide the calming and barrier support the skin needs to tolerate these actives without the protocol having to be paused or reduced.</p><p><strong>Niacinamide (Vitamin B3)</strong> reduces the inflammatory response at the cellular level while simultaneously supporting barrier function and inhibiting melanin transfer — making it uniquely protocol-compatible, as it both soothes and reinforces the depigmentation action. <strong>Centella Asiatica</strong> accelerates barrier recovery and reduces the redness associated with sensitised, peel-compromised skin. <strong>Allantoin</strong> provides immediate comfort by suppressing the inflammatory cascade, while <strong>Panthenol</strong> maintains the moisture levels necessary for a healthy barrier throughout the treatment period. Together, they allow the skin to remain in the protocol without the reactivity that causes patients to stop prematurely.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Noticeable soothing and reduction in the heat and discomfort of sensitised skin. <strong>Days 2–3:</strong> Redness from peeling or treatment reaction visibly reduced. Skin feels more comfortable throughout the day. <strong>Week 2:</strong> Skin is tolerating the protocol consistently — the reactive episodes of the first week settle into a manageable baseline. <strong>Ongoing:</strong> Provides continuous support for the duration of the active treatment phase, allowing the depigmenting actives to do their work without interruption.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Melan Recovery</h3><ol><li>Apply to clean skin morning and evening as your <strong>soothing moisturiser</strong> throughout the active treatment period</li><li>Apply gently — press into skin, do not rub or massage aggressively on sensitised areas</li><li>Use immediately after a peel or pigmentation treatment procedure for instant soothing</li><li>Continue using until redness and sensitivity have fully resolved before transitioning to your regular moisturiser</li><li>Always follow with <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</strong> each morning throughout the protocol</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide (Vitamin B3)</td><td>Reduces cellular inflammation, supports barrier function and inhibits melanin transfer — uniquely protocol-compatible for depigmentation treatment</td></tr><tr><td>Centella Asiatica</td><td>Accelerates barrier recovery and reduces post-peel and post-procedure redness through proven wound-healing mechanisms</td></tr><tr><td>Allantoin</td><td>Immediately suppresses the inflammatory cascade — provides rapid comfort on sensitised, reactive skin</td></tr><tr><td>Panthenol (Vitamin B5)</td><td>Maintains optimal moisture levels throughout treatment — a healthy, hydrated barrier tolerates active protocols more effectively</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The most common reason patients abandon their depigmentation protocol prematurely is discomfort — their skin feels too reactive to continue. Melan Recovery is how I keep patients in their protocols long enough to see real results. It provides exactly the support the skin needs to tolerate the active treatment without compromising what the actives are doing. In my experience, patients who use it consistently complete their protocols at a significantly higher rate — and get significantly better outcomes as a result.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>The first week of my Cosmelan protocol was very uncomfortable. Dr. Bangalee gave me Melan Recovery and within two days my skin had settled enough to carry on. I would have stopped without it.</td><td>I've done two rounds of the Melan Tran3x protocol. The second time I used Melan Recovery throughout and the difference in how my skin felt during treatment was night and day.</td><td>I was worried the depigmentation treatment would make my sensitive skin worse. With this cream it was completely manageable — red for a few days and then fine. Very impressed.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use Melan Recovery during the Cosmelan protocol?</td><td>Yes — it is specifically designed for use alongside Cosmelan and Melan Tran3x protocols. The formula is compatible with the depigmenting actives in both systems. During the initial sensitisation phase of Cosmelan, Melan Recovery provides the soothing support that allows the protocol to continue comfortably.</td></tr><tr><td>What is the difference between Melan Recovery and Fast Skin Repair?</td><td>Melan Recovery is formulated for ongoing daily use during depigmentation protocols — its ingredients are specifically compatible with depigmenting actives and provide continuous soothing support. Fast Skin Repair is an intensive post-procedure recovery cream for the immediate healing phase after Dermapen or deep peels. Both can be prescribed together by Dr. Bangalee for patients going through combined treatment programmes.</td></tr><tr><td>How long do I need to use Melan Recovery?</td><td>For the duration of the active treatment phase — typically 8–16 weeks depending on the protocol. As your skin adapts to the treatment and sensitivity reduces, you can transition to a regular moisturiser. Dr. Bangalee will guide you on timing based on your skin's response at follow-up appointments.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I wear makeup over Melan Recovery?</td><td>Yes — once fully absorbed (approximately 5 minutes), Melan Recovery can be worn under makeup. During active peeling or significant post-procedure sensitisation, a light mineral powder is generally preferable to liquid foundation to reduce irritation risk.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it safe during breastfeeding?</td><td>Melan Recovery does not contain retinoids, high-dose salicylic acid or hydroquinone — the actives most commonly restricted during breastfeeding. However, we always recommend confirming with Dr. Bangalee or your healthcare provider before continuing or starting any treatment protocol during breastfeeding, as the full depigmentation programme involves multiple products.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-melan-recovery';


-- ── 5. Melan Tran3x Concentrate ───────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Concentrate right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have <strong>melasma, post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (PIH), dark spots or age spots</strong> that haven't responded to standard brightening products</li><li>You are left with dark marks after acne, sun exposure or skin inflammation</li><li>Your skin tone is uneven and no amount of coverage makes you feel confident without makeup</li><li>You have been assessed by Dr. Bangalee and recommended for the Melan Tran3x depigmentation protocol</li><li>You want clinical-grade results from a home-care product rather than requiring constant in-clinic treatment</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Concentrate works — the science</h3><p>Most pharmacy brightening serums contain a single active at a modest concentration — they slow melanin production slightly but cannot address the multiple stages of the melanin overproduction cycle. <strong>The Melan Tran3x Concentrate works differently — it targets melanin at three separate stages simultaneously.</strong></p><p><strong>Tranexamic acid</strong> (the Tran3x active) disrupts the signalling between keratinocytes and melanocytes — the cellular conversation that triggers excess melanin production after UV exposure or inflammation. This is a fundamentally different mechanism to most brightening ingredients and is why Tran3x works on skin types and pigmentation patterns that have resisted other treatments. <strong>Niacinamide</strong> blocks the transfer of melanin from the cells that produce it to the cells that display it — fading existing pigmentation while preventing new deposits from forming. <strong>Kojic acid</strong> inhibits tyrosinase — the enzyme directly responsible for melanin synthesis — at the source. <strong>Vitamin C</strong> adds antioxidant protection that reduces the oxidative triggers of UV-induced pigmentation, while its brightening action contributes to overall tone correction. The combination creates a multi-pathway system that no single active can replicate.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Skin tone appears more even overall — early brightening is noticeable even before dark spots begin to visibly fade. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Dark spots begin to visibly lighten — the edges soften first, then the centre fades progressively. <strong>Week 10–12:</strong> Significant reduction in the intensity of hyperpigmentation. Melasma and deeper PIH continue to improve. <strong>Month 4+:</strong> With continued protocol use, most patients achieve their target skin tone. Ongoing low-dose maintenance prevents recurrence.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Concentrate</h3><ol><li>Apply to clean, dry skin each <strong>evening</strong> as your targeted treatment serum step</li><li>Apply a small amount over the entire face — not just spotted areas — to prevent creating a patchy result</li><li>Allow to absorb fully before applying <strong>Melan Recovery</strong> or your prescribed moisturiser</li><li>In the morning: cleanse, apply <strong>Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream</strong>, follow with <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</strong></li><li>Do not skip SPF — without it the protocol's results are significantly undermined</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Tranexamic Acid (Tran3x)</td><td>Disrupts the keratinocyte-melanocyte signalling that triggers excess melanin production — effective on melasma and PIH where other actives fail</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide (Vitamin B3)</td><td>Blocks melanin transfer from producing cells to displaying cells — fades existing spots and prevents new deposits forming</td></tr><tr><td>Kojic Acid</td><td>Inhibits tyrosinase — the enzyme that synthesises melanin — at the source, reducing production capacity</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin C</td><td>Antioxidant brightener that reduces the oxidative UV triggers of pigmentation and contributes to overall tone correction</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Tranexamic acid changed how I approach hyperpigmentation. Before it became available, the options for melasma were limited and often came with significant side effects or rebound pigmentation risks. The Tran3x system gives my patients a safe, effective, multi-pathway protocol that I can calibrate to their specific pigmentation type and skin tone. The Concentrate is the cornerstone — it does the heavy lifting in the evening while the Gel-Cream maintains the action during the day. I prescribe this protocol more than any other product range in the clinic.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I'd had melasma for seven years and tried everything. After three months on the Melan Tran3x protocol with Dr. Bangalee it's reduced by at least 70%. I can finally go out without a full face of foundation.</td><td>The dark marks from my acne were making me so self-conscious. Within six weeks of using this concentrate I could see them genuinely fading — not just being covered up, actually fading. I'm emotional about it honestly.</td><td>I was sceptical because I'd spent a lot on other products that did nothing. This is different. The science behind it makes sense and the results speak for themselves. My skin tone is the most even it's been in fifteen years.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>How long before I see visible results from Melan Tran3x Concentrate?</td><td>Most patients notice improved overall skin brightness within 2–4 weeks. Visible fading of individual dark spots typically begins at 6–8 weeks. Significant, lasting results from melasma or deep PIH require a full 12-week protocol course. Consistency is the critical variable — skipping applications extends the timeline substantially.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it during the day?</td><td>Evening application is recommended. Some ingredients have increased UV sensitivity and the overnight skin repair cycle provides an optimal environment for the actives to work uninterrupted. In the morning, Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream maintains the depigmenting action at a lower daytime concentration, always followed by Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+.</td></tr><tr><td>What makes this different from brightening serums at the pharmacy?</td><td>Most pharmacy serums contain a single active (niacinamide or alpha-arbutin) at cosmetic concentrations. Melan Tran3x Concentrate uses the multi-pathway Tran3x system — tranexamic acid, niacinamide, kojic acid and Vitamin C at pharmaceutical-grade concentrations targeting melanin at three separate stages. It is a cosmeceutical, not a cosmetic, and it is priced and formulated accordingly.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it safe for melasma during pregnancy?</td><td>Melan Tran3x does not contain hydroquinone or retinoids, which are the depigmenting agents most commonly restricted during pregnancy. However, pregnancy-related melasma (chloasma) is hormonally driven and difficult to treat effectively while the hormonal trigger persists. We recommend a consultation with Dr. Bangalee before starting any depigmentation protocol during pregnancy.</td></tr><tr><td>Do I still need SPF during the protocol?</td><td>SPF is absolutely non-negotiable throughout depigmentation treatment. UV exposure is the primary stimulus for melanin overproduction — without daily SPF50+, the protocol is working against the damage you are actively causing by going outdoors unprotected. Mesoprotech Melan 130+ is the prescribed SPF because it also contains active depigmenting ingredients that reinforce the protocol.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-melan-tran3x-concentrate';


-- ── 6. Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream ─────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream right for you?</h3><ul><li>You are on the <strong>Melan Tran3x depigmentation protocol</strong> and need the prescribed daytime maintenance step</li><li>You want a moisturiser that actively works against pigmentation while providing your daily hydration</li><li>You are maintaining results after completing a depigmentation course and want to prevent recurrence</li><li>You have mild-to-moderate uneven skin tone and want a gentle daily brightening moisturiser without a dedicated treatment step</li><li>Your skin type is <strong>normal to oily</strong> — this gel-cream texture is ideal for those who find rich creams too heavy</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream works — the science</h3><p>Depigmentation is not a one-time event — melanin production is a continuous biological process, and without consistent daily suppression the progress made during evening treatment would be gradually reversed by morning. The Gel-Cream provides the <strong>continuous low-dose depigmenting action</strong> that maintains the protocol's gains throughout the day.</p><p>While the Concentrate delivers an intensive evening dose of the Tran3x complex, the Gel-Cream provides the same active system at a concentration calibrated for sustained daily maintenance. <strong>Tranexamic acid</strong> continues suppressing the keratinocyte-melanocyte signalling pathway during the day. <strong>Niacinamide</strong> maintains the block on melanin transfer — the mechanism responsible for the visible appearance of existing dark spots. The <strong>lightweight gel-cream texture</strong> incorporates hyaluronic acid for hydration and absorbs quickly without residue, making it compatible with the SPF that must follow it. The result is a product that multitasks genuinely — daily moisturiser and active treatment step in one formula.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>From first use:</strong> Comfortable, lightweight daily hydration that doesn't interfere with the protocol. <strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Skin tone begins to even as the daytime depigmenting action complements the evening Concentrate. <strong>Month 2–3:</strong> Consistent, maintained results — the improvement from the evening treatment is preserved rather than partially reversed each day. <strong>Maintenance phase:</strong> Used on its own after completing the full protocol, it prevents pigmentation from returning long-term.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream</h3><ol><li>Apply each <strong>morning</strong> to clean skin as your daily moisturiser step — after cleansing and any morning serum</li><li>Apply a small amount over the entire face and neck</li><li>Allow to absorb (2–3 minutes), then apply <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</strong> as the final step</li><li>In the evening, follow the Concentrate protocol as directed by Dr. Bangalee</li><li>During the maintenance phase, can be used on its own morning and evening without the Concentrate</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Tranexamic Acid (Tran3x)</td><td>Maintains the melanin suppression established by the evening Concentrate — prevents daily reversal of protocol gains</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide</td><td>Ongoing block on melanin transfer — preserves the fading of existing spots and prevents new pigmentation forming during the day</td></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Lightweight daily hydration that keeps skin comfortable and plump without the heaviness of a rich cream</td></tr><tr><td>Antioxidants</td><td>Protect against UV-triggered oxidative stress that reactivates melanin production — reinforcing the SPF applied over it</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The Gel-Cream is the daytime anchor of the Melan Tran3x protocol. Patients sometimes think of it as just a moisturiser but it is an active treatment step — it is maintaining the depigmentation work done the night before. Skipping it or substituting a regular moisturiser meaningfully reduces protocol efficacy. After completing the full protocol, I recommend continuing the Gel-Cream as a long-term maintenance product to prevent the pigmentation from returning — especially in patients with hormonally driven melasma, which has a strong tendency to recur without sustained suppression.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I like that my moisturiser is also doing something. I don't have to add extra steps — the Gel-Cream is light, absorbs quickly and I can put my SPF straight over it. Simple and effective.</td><td>I finished the full protocol eight months ago. I still use the Gel-Cream every morning as Dr. Bangalee suggested. My skin tone is the most even it's ever been and the pigmentation hasn't come back.</td><td>Switching from my regular moisturiser to this at the start of my protocol made a noticeable difference to my results. It's not just a vehicle — it's actually doing something all day.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Is this a moisturiser, a treatment, or both?</td><td>It is both simultaneously. The gel-cream provides adequate daily hydration for normal-to-oily skin types, while the Tran3x depigmenting actives continue working against melanin production throughout the day. For most patients on the protocol, it replaces their regular daytime moisturiser entirely.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use the Gel-Cream on its own without the Concentrate?</td><td>Yes — used independently, it is an effective daily brightening moisturiser for mild pigmentation or ongoing maintenance after a completed protocol. For active treatment of significant melasma or PIH, using it alongside the Concentrate (evening) and Mesoprotech SPF (morning) delivers meaningfully better results than the Gel-Cream alone.</td></tr><tr><td>How long do I stay on the full protocol before switching to Gel-Cream maintenance only?</td><td>The active treatment phase is typically 12–16 weeks using both Concentrate and Gel-Cream. After this, Dr. Bangalee will assess your results at a follow-up appointment and advise whether to continue the full protocol, transition to Gel-Cream maintenance only, or cycle on and off depending on your pigmentation pattern and skin response.</td></tr><tr><td>Does it cause sun sensitivity?</td><td>The Gel-Cream does not contain AHAs or retinoids that cause photosensitivity. However, the depigmenting actives work most effectively when UV exposure is blocked — the tranexamic acid system is working against the melanin stimulus that UV exposure provides. SPF is not a precaution but an active part of the protocol.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it on my neck and décolletage for pigmentation there?</td><td>Yes — apply it to the neck and décolletage as part of your morning routine. Pigmentation in these areas responds to the same Tran3x protocol. For more extensive pigmentation across the body, speak to Dr. Bangalee about the most appropriate protocol, as body skin requires different application quantities and may benefit from a different approach.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-melan-tran3x-gel-cream';


-- ── 7. Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+ ─────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoprotech Melan 130+ Pigment Control SPF50+ right for you?</h3><ul><li>You are on a <strong>depigmentation protocol</strong> and need an SPF that reinforces your treatment rather than just protecting against burning</li><li>You have a tendency towards <strong>melasma, dark spots or post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation</strong> and want to prevent them forming</li><li>You want a <strong>single morning product</strong> that provides both SPF50+ protection and active brightening</li><li>You want daily SPF that doesn't leave a white cast, pill under makeup, or feel heavy in Durban's climate</li><li>Your dermatologist or Dr. Bangalee has told you that consistent, daily SPF is non-negotiable for your skin concerns</li></ul><h3>How Mesoprotech Melan 130+ works — the science</h3><p>Most sunscreens block UV — nothing more. Mesoprotech Melan 130+ does both jobs simultaneously: it <strong>blocks the UV stimulus and interrupts the melanin response it triggers</strong>. The name Melan 130+ refers to the clinically designed pigment-control formula — not just an SPF, but a dual-function daily shield for skin with pigmentation concerns.</p><p>UV radiation, particularly UVA (the wavelength that penetrates glass and triggers pigmentation year-round), activates the same keratinocyte-melanocyte signalling pathway that depigmenting treatments are working to suppress. Without SPF, this pathway is re-stimulated every single day — effectively undoing the protocol's work overnight. <strong>Broad-spectrum SPF50+ filters</strong> block both UVA and UVB across the full spectrum at the highest European protection standard. <strong>Tranexamic acid</strong> and <strong>Niacinamide</strong> within the formula continue the depigmenting action of the Melan Tran3x protocol during the hours when the SPF is being worn — so the patient is simultaneously protecting and treating. The <strong>universal tint</strong> provides light coverage that immediately evens tone while the active ingredients work on long-term correction.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Day one:</strong> Improved, even skin tone from the tint — skin looks more refined and uniform immediately. A comfortable, non-greasy texture that sits well under makeup or alone. <strong>Week 2–4 of protocol use:</strong> Maintained depigmentation gains — the progress from the evening treatment is not reversed by morning UV exposure. <strong>Month 2+:</strong> Visible progressive brightening and tone improvement from the daily depigmenting actives in combination with the protocol. <strong>Long-term:</strong> Prevention of new pigmentation and UV-triggered collagen damage — the most valuable outcome is what doesn't appear.</p><h3>How to use Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</h3><ol><li>Apply as the <strong>final step</strong> of your morning skincare routine — after moisturiser and any serums</li><li>Apply generously to the face, neck and any other exposed areas — SPF only works at adequate quantity</li><li>Reapply every <strong>2 hours</strong> during prolonged or direct outdoor exposure</li><li>Use <strong>every day, year-round</strong> — not only on sunny days. UVA penetrates cloud cover and glass</li><li>Continue daily SPF use for at least 6 months after completing any depigmentation protocol</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Broad-Spectrum SPF50+ Filters</td><td>Block UVA and UVB across the full spectrum at the highest European SPF standard — prevents burning and UV-triggered melanin activation simultaneously</td></tr><tr><td>Tranexamic Acid</td><td>Continues the Melan Tran3x protocol's depigmenting action during daytime wear — treatment and protection happen simultaneously</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide</td><td>Maintains block on melanin transfer throughout the day — reinforces both the protocol and the SPF protection</td></tr><tr><td>Universal Tint</td><td>Light pigment coverage that immediately evens and refines skin tone — wears comfortably alone or under makeup</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>I cannot overstate how important SPF is in a pigmentation protocol. Without it, I am treating the same melanin stimulus my patients are recreating every morning on their drive to work. Mesoprotech Melan 130+ is prescribed in every depigmentation protocol I run — not because it is the only SPF available, but because it contains the same Tran3x actives as the protocol. My patient is not just protecting; they are treating for 8–10 hours every day. For patients not on a formal depigmentation protocol, I still recommend it as their daily SPF because of Durban's UV intensity. Prevention is always more effective than correction.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I've avoided SPF for years because everything either left a white cast or pilled under my makeup. This is the first sunscreen I've actually enjoyed wearing. It goes on beautifully and makes my skin look better, not worse.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee was very clear that the SPF was non-negotiable. I understood once I saw how the science works — I was undoing the protocol every morning. Since using Melan 130+ consistently my results have improved dramatically.</td><td>I use it as my base before foundation. The tint evens out my skin tone and I actually use less foundation than I used to. The SPF is a bonus — the skin-evening effect alone would be worth buying it for.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use this as my only daily SPF even when I'm not treating pigmentation?</td><td>Yes — it is an excellent daily SPF for anyone. The broad-spectrum SPF50+ provides the same high-level UV protection needed every day, with the added benefit of progressive skin-tone improvement from the depigmenting actives. It is particularly well-suited to Durban's year-round UV intensity.</td></tr><tr><td>Does the tint suit darker South African skin tones?</td><td>The tint is a light, universal formula designed to blend across a range of skin tones. On lighter tones it provides a subtle coverage finish. On medium to deeper tones the tint effect is minimal — a light brightening result rather than a colour match. For a precise colour finish on deeper skin tones, apply a mineral foundation or powder over the SPF after it has set.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I apply makeup directly over it?</td><td>Yes — apply it as the final skincare step, allow 2–3 minutes to set, then apply foundation, concealer or powder as normal. Its non-greasy finish is compatible with most foundation formulas without affecting wear or finish.</td></tr><tr><td>Do I need to reapply SPF during the day?</td><td>For indoor use with incidental sun exposure, a single morning application is adequate. For outdoor activities or continuous direct sun exposure, reapply every 2 hours. No SPF — regardless of the number — provides all-day protection from a single morning application under real outdoor conditions.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it water-resistant for swimming or sport?</td><td>It has light water-resistance suitable for everyday perspiration and incidental water contact. It is not formulated as an activity-grade water-resistant sunscreen. For swimming or prolonged outdoor sport, reapply immediately after water exposure or use a dedicated water-resistant SPF for activity and Melan 130+ for your daily urban wear.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-mesoprotech-melan-130-pigment-control-spf50';


-- ── 8. Brightening Foam ───────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Brightening Foam right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin looks dull, tired or grey and your current cleanser is not making a difference</li><li>You have <strong>uneven texture, enlarged pores or persistent congestion</strong> that regular cleansers don't address</li><li>You are on a brightening or depigmentation protocol and want to maximise the penetration of your treatment products</li><li>You are in your mid-20s or older and noticing that skin cell turnover is slower — complexion less bright and smooth than it was</li><li>You want a clinically active cleanser that does more than just remove makeup</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Brightening Foam works — the science</h3><p>Most cleansers perform a single function: removing surface debris. The skin's dullness, uneven texture and product absorption problems, however, come from what stays behind — the accumulated layer of dead corneocytes that the skin's natural exfoliation process fails to remove quickly enough from the mid-20s onwards. <strong>Brightening Foam addresses this at the chemical level during every cleanse.</strong></p><p><strong>Glycolic acid</strong> is the smallest alpha-hydroxy acid (AHA) molecule — small enough to penetrate effectively through a cleanser's brief contact time. It works by dissolving the desmosomes — the protein bonds that hold dead skin cells to the surface — allowing them to be rinsed away rather than accumulating. This process, repeated daily, progressively reveals the fresher, brighter skin cells beneath and prevents the layer of dead cell buildup that causes dullness, uneven texture and blocked pore openings. Importantly, because it is a rinse-off formula, the concentration of glycolic acid delivers exfoliation without the sustained-contact irritation risk of leave-on AHA products. <strong>Niacinamide</strong> reinforces the action with ongoing brightening and barrier-calming properties, making the formula suitable for daily use even on moderately sensitive skin.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>After first use:</strong> Skin feels smoother and cleaner — a different quality of clean compared to a standard cleanser. Slight brightness improvement noticeable immediately. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Progressive improvement in skin texture and luminosity. Pores appear cleaner and smaller. <strong>Month 1:</strong> Clearer, more even complexion. Serums and treatment products visibly absorbing better. <strong>Month 2+:</strong> Consistent brightening and refined texture — the foundation of an effective routine.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Brightening Foam</h3><ol><li>Apply a small amount to <strong>damp skin</strong> each morning — or morning and evening for those with resilient skin</li><li>Massage gently in circular motions for 30–60 seconds, avoiding the eye area</li><li>Rinse thoroughly with lukewarm water and pat dry</li><li>If new to AHA cleansers, begin with <strong>alternate days</strong> and build to daily use over 2 weeks as skin acclimatises</li><li>Always follow with SPF in the morning — AHA use increases UV sensitivity and SPF is mandatory</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Glycolic Acid (AHA)</td><td>Dissolves the protein bonds holding dead skin cells to the surface — reveals brighter, smoother skin with every daily cleanse</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide</td><td>Calms any post-exfoliation sensitivity and provides ongoing brightening action — makes the formula suitable for daily sensitive skin use</td></tr><tr><td>Amino Acid Surfactants</td><td>Gentle, pH-matched cleansing agents that remove impurities without stripping the skin barrier or leaving a residue that would block product absorption</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The cleanser step is where most patients lose results they don't know they're losing. If you are applying excellent treatment products to skin that hasn't been properly prepared, the absorption and efficacy are compromised from the start. I recommend Brightening Foam as the morning cleanser for any patient on a brightening or depigmentation protocol — the glycolic acid preparation step measurably improves the penetration of everything that follows. It is also the first recommendation I make to patients who come in asking why their skincare isn't working.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I didn't realise how much my old cleanser was holding back my routine. Since switching to this, my serum seems to be working so much better and my skin is genuinely brighter by mid-morning — not just right after cleansing.</td><td>I have acne-prone skin and was worried about anything new. This has been brilliant — my pores look smaller and the post-acne marks are fading faster since I started using it. Really happy with it.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee told me to start here before anything else. I was doubtful a cleanser would make that much difference. Three weeks later my skin tone is noticeably more even and my makeup goes on so much more smoothly.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I use Brightening Foam every day, or only a few times per week?</td><td>Once your skin has acclimatised (typically 2 weeks of alternate-day use), daily use is appropriate for most skin types. If you experience persistent dryness or sensitivity, reduce frequency and ensure you are following with adequate moisturiser and SPF. Oily and resilient skin types can often use it twice daily without issue.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it suitable for acne-prone skin?</td><td>Yes — glycolic acid is beneficial for acne-prone skin as it unclogs the pore openings that trap sebum, reduces dead cell buildup that contributes to comedone formation, and accelerates the fading of post-acne hyperpigmentation. It is particularly effective when paired with depigmenting serums for PIH left by breakouts.</td></tr><tr><td>Will it cause visible skin peeling or flaking?</td><td>At the concentration in this rinse-off cleanser formula, visible peeling is not expected. Glycolic acid is active during contact but is rinsed off before causing the sustained-contact exfoliation that produces visible flaking. Temporary mild sensitivity or tightness is possible in the first 1–2 weeks as your skin adjusts.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it while I'm on the Melan Tran3x protocol?</td><td>Yes — it is a recommended preparatory step in the protocol. Exfoliating the surface before applying treatment products improves their penetration and efficacy measurably. If you are in the initial sensitised phase of the Cosmelan protocol, confirm with Dr. Bangalee before introducing a new exfoliating product.</td></tr><tr><td>At what age should I start using an AHA cleanser?</td><td>AHA cleansers are generally appropriate from age 18 onwards. In younger skin, natural cell turnover is rapid enough that AHA assistance is rarely necessary. From the mid-20s, turnover begins to slow — this is when dullness and texture changes typically begin — making Brightening Foam an ideal preventive addition to a maturing skincare routine.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-brightening-foam';


-- ── 9. Hydracream Fusion ──────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Hydracream Fusion right for you?</h3><ul><li>Your skin feels <strong>persistently tight, rough or uncomfortable</strong> despite regular moisturising</li><li>You have <strong>genuinely dry skin</strong> — not just dehydrated — with a compromised barrier that cannot hold moisture</li><li>Your skin is recovering from intensive procedures (Dermapen, peels) and needs richer nourishment than a standard moisturiser provides</li><li>You are in a dry or air-conditioned environment that depletes skin moisture faster than normal</li><li>You have tried lightweight moisturisers without success and need something that delivers real, lasting nourishment</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Hydracream Fusion works — the science</h3><p>Dry skin is not simply a moisture deficit — it is a <strong>barrier deficit</strong>. The skin's outermost layer (the stratum corneum) is held together by a mortar of lipids — primarily ceramides — that prevents water from evaporating and keeps environmental irritants out. When this lipid layer is depleted, water escapes faster than the skin can replenish it, and the result is persistent dryness that basic hydrating moisturisers only temporarily mask.</p><p><strong>Hydracream Fusion addresses the structural cause.</strong> <strong>Ceramides</strong> — the actual lipid molecules of the skin barrier — are replenished directly, rebuilding the mortar that holds barrier cells together and restoring the skin's own moisture-retaining capacity rather than supplementing it from outside. <strong>Shea butter</strong> provides complementary emollient protection, softening and sealing the surface while the ceramides work at a structural level. <strong>Hyaluronic acid</strong> binds water within the dermal layers for sustained, deep hydration. <strong>Vitamin E</strong> provides antioxidant protection against the oxidative damage that degrades barrier lipids. The result is a cream that progressively improves the skin's ability to stay hydrated independently, rather than requiring constant heavy application to maintain comfort.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>After first application:</strong> Immediate comfort — tightness and roughness ease within minutes of application. Skin feels genuinely nourished rather than temporarily coated. <strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Tightness episodes reduce in frequency. Skin retains moisture for longer between applications. <strong>Month 1:</strong> Noticeably softer, smoother skin texture. Reduced reactivity and sensitivity. <strong>Month 2+:</strong> Improved independent moisture retention — skin needs less product to stay comfortable as barrier function is progressively restored.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Hydracream Fusion</h3><ol><li>Apply to clean, dry skin morning and/or evening as your primary moisturiser step</li><li>Use after any serums — apply to the face, neck and décolletage</li><li>Allow to absorb before applying SPF in the morning</li><li>For very dry or post-procedure skin, apply a more generous layer as an <strong>overnight nourishing treatment</strong></li><li>During intensive treatment recovery, use in combination with <strong>Fast Skin Repair</strong> as directed by Dr. Bangalee</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Ceramides</td><td>Replenish the structural lipids of the skin barrier — rebuild moisture retention capacity at the source rather than masking dryness at the surface</td></tr><tr><td>Shea Butter</td><td>Emollient protection that softens and seals the skin surface while ceramides rebuild deeper barrier function</td></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Binds water within dermal layers for sustained, deep hydration that doesn't evaporate through a compromised barrier</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin E</td><td>Antioxidant protection against oxidative degradation of barrier lipids — preserves the ceramide complex and nourishes skin at the same time</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>Dry skin patients often make the mistake of using more and more moisturiser without addressing why the moisture isn't being retained. Hydracream Fusion is what I reach for when a patient's barrier is genuinely compromised — post-procedure, chronically dry, or stripped by over-cleansing or over-exfoliation. The ceramide complex rebuilds moisture retention from the inside out; within three to four weeks, most patients need significantly less product to maintain the same level of comfort. It is also my first recommendation for post-Dermapen skin in patients with a dry baseline — Fast Skin Repair in the acute phase, then Hydracream Fusion for sustained barrier support.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I've used expensive moisturisers my whole life and my skin always felt tight by midday. Hydracream Fusion is the first one that has actually changed that. Two months in and I can feel the difference in how my skin holds moisture on its own.</td><td>After my chemical peel my skin was so dry and uncomfortable. Dr. Bangalee recommended this alongside Fast Skin Repair. The combination was extraordinary — my skin was back to normal so much faster than after my previous peel.</td><td>Living in air conditioning all day destroyed my skin barrier. This cream was genuinely life-changing. My skin was uncomfortable and reactive all the time — now it's calm and soft and I don't think about it anymore. That's all I wanted.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Is Hydracream Fusion suitable for oily or combination skin?</td><td>It is formulated primarily for dry and dehydrated skin types and may feel too rich for oily skin during the day. However, oily skin with a compromised barrier — a common result of over-cleansing or over-exfoliation — can benefit from a nightly application. For combination skin, apply to dry areas (cheeks, neck) while using a lighter moisturiser on oilier zones.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it as an overnight mask?</td><td>Yes — applying a generous layer as an overnight treatment is one of the most effective ways to use it for very dry skin. The skin's overnight repair cycle works synergistically with a ceramide-rich cream, and the sustained contact time allows maximum lipid replenishment. Apply the last step before sleep and rinse any excess in the morning if preferred.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it fragrance-free?</td><td>The formula is developed to minimise irritant risk and is suitable for sensitive skin. If you have confirmed fragrance allergies or are recovering from a procedure that has significantly sensitised your skin, raise this with Dr. Bangalee before introducing any new moisturiser.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it during pregnancy?</td><td>Hydracream Fusion does not contain retinoids, high-dose salicylic acid or other actives typically restricted during pregnancy. Its ceramide, shea butter and hyaluronic acid base is generally considered safe and beneficial for pregnant skin, which is often drier and more sensitive. Confirm with your healthcare provider as a precaution.</td></tr><tr><td>What is the difference between this and a regular pharmacy moisturiser?</td><td>Standard pharmacy moisturisers provide surface hydration through humectants and occlusives — they add water and slow its loss temporarily. Hydracream Fusion replenishes ceramides — the actual structural lipids of the skin barrier — which rebuilds the barrier's capacity to retain moisture independently. The improvement compounds over time rather than requiring constant reapplication.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-hydracream-fusion';


-- ── 10. Melan Tranex Kit ──────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is the Mesoestetic Melan Tranex Kit right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have been assessed by Dr. Bangalee and recommended the <strong>Melan Tran3x depigmentation protocol</strong></li><li>You want to start a complete, structured at-home depigmentation system with everything in one purchase</li><li>You have <strong>melasma, post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, dark spots or age spots</strong> that have resisted standard brightening products</li><li>You want a clinically validated home protocol that mirrors the approach used in professional aesthetic clinics</li><li>You are committed to the full protocol — consistent use morning and evening for a minimum of 12 weeks</li></ul><h3>How the Melan Tranex Kit works — the science</h3><p>Individual brightening products address single aspects of melanin production. The Melan Tran3x system is different — it is a <strong>coordinated multi-product protocol</strong> where each component targets a different stage of the melanin overproduction cycle, and the combination achieves results that no single product can replicate.</p><p>The protocol works around the clock. In the evening, the <strong>Concentrate</strong> delivers the intensive Tran3x active system — tranexamic acid disrupting the UV-triggered melanin signalling pathway, niacinamide blocking melanin transfer, kojic acid inhibiting tyrosinase at the source. While the skin's overnight repair cycle is active, the Concentrate drives deep cellular-level correction. In the morning, the <strong>Gel-Cream</strong> maintains the suppression established the night before — preventing the daily UV stimulus from reactivating what the evening treatment worked to correct. The <strong>Mesoprotech SPF50+</strong> then blocks the UV trigger at the source and continues the depigmenting action for the remaining hours of the day. The result is continuous, 24-hour melanin management — not the intermittent activity of a single product applied once daily.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Overall skin brightness improves — tone appears more even even before individual dark spots begin to visibly fade. Skin texture often improves simultaneously from the cleansing and preparation steps. <strong>Week 6–8:</strong> Dark spots begin to soften and lighten — edges fade first, then centres progressively. <strong>Week 10–12:</strong> Significant reduction in pigmentation intensity visible to others, not just yourself. <strong>Month 4+:</strong> Completion of the active treatment phase and transition to long-term maintenance using Gel-Cream and SPF to prevent recurrence.</p><h3>The Melan Tranex Kit Protocol</h3><ol><li><strong>Morning:</strong> Cleanse → Melan Tran3x Gel-Cream → Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</li><li><strong>Evening:</strong> Cleanse → Melan Tran3x Concentrate → Melan Recovery (if sensitised) or regular moisturiser</li><li>Use <strong>every single day without exception</strong> for a minimum of 12 weeks — consistency determines results</li><li><strong>SPF is mandatory</strong> every morning — without it the protocol is working against the melanin stimulus you recreate outdoors</li><li>Consider adding <strong>Brightening Foam</strong> as your morning cleanser to improve penetration of the treatment actives</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Tranexamic Acid (Tran3x)</td><td>Core active of both the Concentrate and Gel-Cream — disrupts the UV-triggered melanin signalling pathway that drives melasma and PIH</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide</td><td>Present in multiple protocol products — blocks melanin transfer at every stage of the day and supports barrier function</td></tr><tr><td>Kojic Acid</td><td>In the Concentrate — inhibits tyrosinase at the source to reduce melanin production capacity</td></tr><tr><td>SPF50+ Broad-Spectrum Filters</td><td>In the Mesoprotech SPF — blocks the UV trigger that drives melanin overproduction, making protection and treatment simultaneous</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The Melan Tranex Kit is how I start most new pigmentation patients who aren't ready for an in-clinic treatment yet, or who want to see how their skin responds to the Tran3x system first. The protocol works — but it only works if every component is used consistently and the SPF is worn every morning without exception. I tell every patient the same thing: the SPF is not optional. It is the third leg of the protocol. Without it, you are treating the melanin stimulus I am helping you suppress. The kit makes it easy to have everything in place from day one.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I was nervous about committing to a whole protocol but the kit made it simple — everything was there and Dr. Bangalee explained how to use it. By week ten my skin was genuinely transformed. I'm still maintaining with the Gel-Cream and SPF.</td><td>I've spent more money on individual brightening products that did nothing than this kit cost. This actually worked. Following the protocol exactly made all the difference — the morning and evening combination is what I was missing before.</td><td>The melasma I've had since my second pregnancy has faded more in three months with this kit than in three years of everything else I tried. The protocol approach is what makes it different from just buying a serum.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>What products are included in the Melan Tranex Kit?</td><td>The kit contains the core components of the Melan Tran3x protocol: the treatment Concentrate, the daily Gel-Cream and the Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+. Contact Star Aesthetic Centre to confirm the exact current kit composition, as mesoestetic periodically updates kit configurations. Melan Recovery (soothing support) and Brightening Foam (preparation cleanser) are available separately and recommended alongside the kit by Dr. Bangalee.</td></tr><tr><td>How long does the kit last?</td><td>Most patients find the kit provides a 6–8 week supply when following the protocol as directed. Since a full treatment course is 12–16 weeks, plan to purchase a second kit to complete the programme. The cost per week is significantly lower when purchased as a kit versus individual products.</td></tr><tr><td>Do I need a consultation before starting?</td><td>A consultation with Dr. Bangalee is strongly recommended, particularly for melasma — which has multiple subtypes (epidermal, dermal, mixed) that respond differently to treatment. He will assess your specific pigmentation pattern, skin tone and overall skin health to ensure the Melan Tran3x protocol is the right approach, and identify whether an in-clinic treatment would accelerate your results significantly.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use the kit without having had an in-clinic treatment?</td><td>Yes — the kit is a standalone at-home protocol and does not require prior in-clinic treatment. However, combining it with Dr. Bangalee's in-clinic treatments (Cosmelan peel, chemical peels, Dermapen) significantly accelerates results. In-clinic treatments reach deeper levels of pigmentation that topical products alone cannot resolve within a standard course.</td></tr><tr><td>How soon will I see visible results?</td><td>Most patients notice improved brightness and skin tone within 4–6 weeks. Visible dark spot reduction is typically evident by 8–12 weeks. Results depend on pigmentation type and depth, consistency of use and SPF application. Deep melasma or long-standing PIH may require a longer protocol or the addition of in-clinic treatment to resolve fully.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-melan-tranex-kit';


-- ── 11. Cosmelan 2 Maintenance Cream ─────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Cosmelan 2 Maintenance Cream right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have completed — or are scheduled for — the <strong>professional Cosmelan depigmentation peel</strong> at Star Aesthetic Centre with Dr. Bangalee</li><li>You want to <strong>protect and extend the results</strong> of your in-clinic Cosmelan investment</li><li>You understand that the maintenance phase is as important as the peel itself in preventing pigmentation from returning</li><li>You have been prescribed Cosmelan 2 by Dr. Bangalee as part of your post-peel home care protocol</li></ul><p><em>Cosmelan 2 is a prescription maintenance product. It is only appropriate for patients who have had the professional Cosmelan peel. If you are interested in the Cosmelan treatment, contact us on +27 (0)31 573 1325 or via WhatsApp to arrange a consultation with Dr. Bangalee.</em></p><h3>How Mesoestetic Cosmelan 2 works — the science</h3><p>The Cosmelan system is a two-phase professional treatment. Phase one — the in-clinic Cosmelan mask applied by Dr. Bangalee — initiates a powerful depigmenting process that delivers results unachievable with home-care products alone. <strong>Cosmelan 2 is phase two: the essential maintenance that determines whether those results last.</strong></p><p>Melanin overproduction is a chronic condition, not a one-time event. The melanocytes that produced excess pigmentation remain in place after the peel — and without continuous suppression, they will resume activity, triggered by UV exposure, hormonal fluctuations and inflammation. <strong>4-Butylresorcinol</strong> — a premium tyrosinase inhibitor significantly more potent than kojic acid — maintains continuous suppression of melanin synthesis at the enzyme level. <strong>Kojic acid</strong> adds a secondary inhibitory pathway, while <strong>Phytic acid</strong> chelates the copper ions that activate the tyrosinase enzyme itself. <strong>Tranexamic acid</strong> prevents the UV-triggered signalling that would reactivate the melanocytes. Together, they form a multi-mechanism maintenance system that holds the melanocytes in a suppressed state as their activity gradually normalises to a healthy baseline over months of consistent use.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Weeks 1–4 post-peel:</strong> Continued improvement and brightening as the peel's depigmenting effect continues under maintenance support. Skin is stabilising and sensitivity is reducing. <strong>Month 2–3:</strong> Results from the peel are fully consolidated — dark spots significantly reduced or resolved. Skin tone even and luminous. <strong>Month 4–6:</strong> Frequency of Cosmelan 2 application is progressively reduced as directed — the skin is maintaining its correction more independently. <strong>Month 6–12:</strong> Transition to long-term prevention at minimal frequency, or completion of the maintenance programme if Dr. Bangalee assesses the results as stable.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Cosmelan 2 Maintenance Cream</h3><ol><li>Use <strong>exactly as prescribed by Dr. Bangalee</strong> — frequency and quantity are personalised and adjusted throughout the maintenance phase</li><li>Apply in the <strong>evening</strong> after cleansing as prescribed</li><li>Begin at the prescribed frequency (typically daily in phase one) and reduce gradually as directed at follow-up appointments</li><li>Apply <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+ every morning</strong> without exception throughout the entire Cosmelan programme</li><li>Contact Star Aesthetic Centre immediately if you experience unexpected severe irritation, excessive peeling or other concerning reactions</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>4-Butylresorcinol</td><td>Premium tyrosinase inhibitor — more potent than kojic acid; maintains continuous suppression of melanin synthesis at the enzyme level throughout the maintenance phase</td></tr><tr><td>Kojic Acid</td><td>Secondary tyrosinase inhibitor — adds a complementary pathway to maintain melanin suppression and prevent recurrence</td></tr><tr><td>Phytic Acid</td><td>Chelates the copper ions that activate tyrosinase — removes the co-factor the melanin-producing enzyme needs to function</td></tr><tr><td>Tranexamic Acid</td><td>Prevents UV-triggered keratinocyte-melanocyte signalling that would reactivate the melanocytes between peel sessions</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The Cosmelan peel is the most powerful depigmentation treatment I offer, and the results are genuinely transformative for the right patient. But I am equally clear with every patient before we begin: the maintenance phase is not optional. The in-clinic peel initiates the correction — Cosmelan 2 consolidates and protects it. Patients who follow the maintenance programme as prescribed maintain their results long-term. Patients who stop early — usually because their skin looks so good they assume it's fixed — typically see recurrence within 3–6 months, particularly with melasma. The melanocytes need sustained suppression to normalise. I prescribe and supervise this programme personally for every Cosmelan patient.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I'd had melasma for twelve years. After the Cosmelan peel and the full maintenance programme with Cosmelan 2 it has virtually gone. I cannot believe the difference. Dr. Bangalee's guidance throughout made it manageable.</td><td>The peel was intense for the first week but the results were worth every uncomfortable day. The maintenance cream kept everything I'd gained and now, two years later, my skin is the clearest it's ever been.</td><td>I was very nervous about doing the peel. Dr. Bangalee explained everything and the Cosmelan 2 maintenance made the recovery phase much more comfortable than I expected. My skin tone has changed completely.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>What is the Cosmelan professional peel?</td><td>The Cosmelan peel is a two-stage professional depigmentation treatment performed at Star Aesthetic Centre. Dr. Bangalee applies a concentrated Cosmelan mask in-clinic, initiating a powerful depigmenting process that reaches deeper levels of hyperpigmentation than home-care products can address. Cosmelan 2 is the essential home maintenance phase that protects and extends those results. Contact us on +27 (0)31 573 1325 to arrange a consultation.</td></tr><tr><td>How long do I need to use Cosmelan 2 after the peel?</td><td>The maintenance programme typically runs for 6–12 months, depending on your pigmentation type and skin response. Phase one (months 1–3) involves daily application. Dr. Bangalee progressively reduces the frequency over subsequent months as your results consolidate. Some patients continue at very low frequency indefinitely as a preventive measure, particularly those with hormonally driven melasma.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I stop using it once my skin looks clear?</td><td>Stopping prematurely is the most common cause of recurrence after the Cosmelan peel. Visible clearing does not mean the melanocytes have normalised — they remain in a suppressed state that requires maintained treatment. Follow Dr. Bangalee's programme to its completion. The decreasing frequency protocol is specifically designed to withdraw gradually as the skin achieves independent stability.</td></tr><tr><td>What if I miss several applications?</td><td>Occasional missed applications will not significantly affect results. Prolonged gaps — particularly in the first three months of maintenance — allow melanin production to reactivate, especially with UV exposure. Resume as soon as possible and contact Star Aesthetic Centre if you have missed more than two weeks so Dr. Bangalee can assess whether the programme needs adjustment.</td></tr><tr><td>Is the Cosmelan system suitable for all South African skin tones?</td><td>The Cosmelan system has been extensively used across all skin tones including darker Fitzpatrick IV–VI skin types common in South Africa. Approach and concentration are adjusted based on skin tone and pigmentation type. Dr. Bangalee evaluates each patient individually — a thorough consultation is essential before the Cosmelan peel, both to confirm suitability and to ensure the protocol is calibrated for your specific skin type and pigmentation pattern.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-cosmelan-2-maintenance-cream';


-- ── 12. Hydratonic Mist ───────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic Hydratonic Mist right for you?</h3><ul><li>You want to <strong>improve serum absorption</strong> without adding complexity to your routine</li><li>Your skin feels dry or tight during the day — particularly in air-conditioned environments common in Durban's offices and malls</li><li>You are on an intensive treatment protocol and your skin needs frequent hydration top-ups</li><li>You want a product you can use <strong>over or under makeup</strong> to refresh and revitalise throughout the day</li><li>You have just had an in-clinic treatment and need an immediate, gentle soothing step</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic Hydratonic Mist works — the science</h3><p>There is a counterintuitive truth about misting plain water onto the skin: it temporarily worsens dehydration. As the droplets evaporate from the skin surface, they draw moisture from the upper epidermal layers with them — leaving skin more dehydrated than before. <strong>Hydratonic Mist is formulated to do the opposite.</strong></p><p><strong>Hyaluronic acid</strong> in the mist format creates a different dynamic: when applied to the skin, HA molecules bind to water and hold it on and within the surface — preventing the evaporative loss that makes plain water misting counterproductive. The spray mechanism delivers HA in a uniformly dispersed fine mist that contacts the skin more evenly than finger application, providing consistent surface hydration across the entire face. <strong>Aloe vera</strong> adds immediate soothing and anti-inflammatory action — particularly valuable post-procedure when the skin is reactive. <strong>Panthenol (Vitamin B5)</strong> supports the barrier's own water-attracting function, enhancing how the skin retains the hydration delivered. Applied before a serum, the lightly hydrated surface improves penetration measurably — the active ingredients of treatment products distribute more evenly and absorb more readily into a hydrated skin surface than a dry one.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Refreshed, more comfortable skin — the tight or dry feeling that builds throughout the day is relieved within seconds. A visible freshness and brightness to the complexion. <strong>Throughout the day:</strong> Used as a mid-day refresh, the mist resets the skin's moisture balance without disrupting makeup. <strong>As a routine prep step:</strong> Serums applied after the mist absorb more evenly and the results of treatment products are enhanced over time. <strong>Post-treatment:</strong> Immediate soothing relief after in-clinic procedures.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic Hydratonic Mist</h3><ol><li><strong>As a toner step:</strong> Mist over clean skin after cleansing and before serums — allow to absorb for 30 seconds before applying your serum</li><li><strong>Mid-day refresh:</strong> Mist over the face at any point during the day — over or under makeup</li><li><strong>Post-treatment:</strong> Apply immediately after clinic procedures for instant soothing and cooling comfort</li><li>Hold the bottle <strong>20–30 cm</strong> from the face for an even, fine mist — not a concentrated spray</li><li>Allow to absorb naturally or pat gently — do not rub</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Binds water to the skin surface on contact — prevents the evaporative loss that makes plain water misting counterproductive and provides genuine lasting hydration</td></tr><tr><td>Aloe Vera</td><td>Immediate soothing and anti-inflammatory action — particularly effective for post-procedure comfort and reactive skin states</td></tr><tr><td>Panthenol (Vitamin B5)</td><td>Supports the barrier's water-attracting function — enhances how effectively the skin retains the hydration the mist delivers</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The Hydratonic Mist is in my clinic's post-treatment trolley. After every procedure we apply it immediately for soothing and cooling — patients notice the comfort difference instantly. At home, I recommend it to patients on intensive protocols whose skin is going through a reactive phase, and to those in Durban's air-conditioned environments where transepidermal water loss is consistently elevated. Used before a serum, it genuinely improves the feel of application and, over time, the efficacy of treatment products — the difference between applying actives to parched skin versus a properly hydrated canvas.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I work in a fully air-conditioned office and my skin was so uncomfortable by 3pm every day. I keep this on my desk now. Two spritzes and it resets completely. I use it five times a day some days — it's become essential.</td><td>I spray it on before my Melan Tran3x serum every evening and then before my SPF in the morning. I'm not sure if it's the mist or just using the protocol better but my skin has been responding really well since I started.</td><td>Dr. Bangalee applied it right after my Dermapen treatment in the clinic. It felt amazing on the hot, sensitive skin immediately after needling. I bought it to use at home in the days after and it made the recovery much more comfortable.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Can I spray the Hydratonic Mist over my makeup during the day?</td><td>Yes — hold the bottle at least 25 cm from the face, close your eyes, and apply a single pass in a fine mist. Allow to absorb naturally for a refreshed, slightly dewy finish. Avoid applying heavily directly onto thick liquid foundation, as excess moisture can cause slippage. A single light mist refreshes without disturbing most makeup formulas.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it just water, or does it actually do something?</td><td>It contains hyaluronic acid, aloe vera and panthenol — not water. Plain water sprayed on the skin actually draws moisture out as it evaporates, worsening dehydration. The HA in Hydratonic Mist binds water to the skin surface rather than evaporating, providing genuine lasting hydration rather than temporary cooling.</td></tr><tr><td>How many times per day can I use it?</td><td>There is no upper limit — it can be used as often as needed. Most patients use it 2–4 times: as a morning toner step, once or twice during the day and occasionally before an evening serum. During post-procedure recovery, some patients use it more frequently for soothing comfort.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it directly after a chemical peel or Dermapen?</td><td>Yes — it is one of the gentlest products in the mesoestetic range. The aloe vera and panthenol provide excellent immediate soothing on sensitised post-procedure skin. Avoid applying over broken or actively oozing skin. Confirm with Dr. Bangalee before using any new product during the first 48 hours of acute post-procedure recovery.</td></tr><tr><td>Does it work as a makeup setting spray?</td><td>It is not specifically formulated as a setting spray. However, many patients find a light mist over completed makeup gives a natural, skin-like finish. For maximum makeup longevity in Durban's heat and humidity, a dedicated setting spray as the final step gives better hold. Use Hydratonic Mist as your skincare preparation step and a setting spray for makeup fixation.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-hydratonic-mist';


-- ── 13. HA Densimatrix ────────────────────────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic HA Densimatrix right for you?</h3><ul><li>You are seeing <strong>fine lines, loss of firmness or a flattened, less voluminous appearance</strong> to your face</li><li>Your skin looks dehydrated and dull despite regular moisturising — lightweight products aren't reaching the depth needed</li><li>You have filler or skin-booster treatments with Dr. Bangalee and want to <strong>maintain and extend those results</strong> between appointments</li><li>You want the plumping and volumising effect of hyaluronic acid working at every skin depth, not just the surface</li><li>You are committed to a daily anti-ageing serum and want one with serious clinical backing</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic HA Densimatrix works — the science</h3><p>Hyaluronic acid is the skin's primary structural hydrator — a molecule capable of binding 1,000 times its weight in water, providing the turgor and volume that makes young skin look plump and firm. By the mid-30s, the skin's HA production declines measurably; by 60, it has reduced by more than half. The result is the gradual deflation, line formation and loss of skin density that characterises facial ageing. <strong>HA Densimatrix replaces what the skin stops making — at every level.</strong></p><p>The critical innovation is <strong>multi-level delivery</strong>. Hyaluronic acid molecules of different sizes penetrate to different depths: large molecules cannot pass through the skin barrier and act at the surface; medium molecules reach the epidermis and superficial dermis; nano-HA is small enough to penetrate to the deep dermis. Most HA serums contain a single molecular weight — they hydrate at one level only. HA Densimatrix uses <strong>three distinct molecular weights simultaneously</strong>. High molecular weight HA creates a moisture-binding film on the surface for immediate plumping and smoothing. Medium molecular weight HA penetrates to the mid-layers for volumising and firming support. <strong>Nano-HA</strong> reaches the deep dermis — and at this depth, it does not merely hydrate: it <strong>stimulates the skin's own fibroblasts to produce new HA</strong>, progressively rebuilding the density that was lost. The peptides in the formula simultaneously activate collagen and elastin synthesis, reinforcing the structural matrix that gives skin its firmness. The result is a serum that works like a professional skin booster — but compounding with every daily application.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Within days:</strong> Visible surface plumping — skin looks fuller and fine lines appear softened. Skin feels deeply hydrated rather than superficially coated. <strong>Week 3–4:</strong> Improved firmness at the mid-face — skin feels more supported and lifted. <strong>Month 2:</strong> Visible improvement in fine line depth. Skin has a naturally voluminous quality that it hadn't before. <strong>Month 3+:</strong> Deep dermis restructuring compounds — the skin's own HA production is being stimulated, leading to progressive improvement that continues with consistent daily use.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic HA Densimatrix</h3><ol><li>Apply 3–4 drops to clean skin each <strong>evening</strong> as your first serum step</li><li>Press gently into the face, neck and décolletage — do not rub</li><li>Allow to absorb fully (1–2 minutes), then follow with <strong>Hydracream Fusion</strong> or your prescribed moisturiser to seal in the hydration</li><li>For enhanced anti-ageing results, also apply in the morning under <strong>Aox Ferulic</strong> and SPF</li><li>Use consistently — the deep-dermis fibroblast stimulation effect compounds over months of daily use</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>High Molecular Weight HA</td><td>Creates a moisture-binding film on the skin surface — immediate visible plumping, smoothing and reduction of fine line depth</td></tr><tr><td>Medium Molecular Weight HA</td><td>Penetrates the epidermis and superficial dermis — volumises and firms from the mid-layers of the skin</td></tr><tr><td>Nano-HA (Low Molecular Weight)</td><td>Penetrates to the deep dermis — stimulates fibroblasts to produce new HA, rebuilding the density lost through ageing</td></tr><tr><td>Peptides</td><td>Signal proteins that activate collagen and elastin synthesis — reinforce the structural matrix alongside the HA volumising effect</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>HA Densimatrix is the daily home care product I pair with every skin-booster and filler treatment I perform. The in-clinic treatment delivers a concentrated HA depot at the tissue level; HA Densimatrix maintains and extends that effect at the cellular level every day between appointments. Patients who use it consistently need less filler volume and achieve better overall skin quality results — the skin is genuinely more hydrated and structurally supported at every appointment. For patients not yet ready for in-clinic treatment, it is the highest-impact anti-ageing serum in the mesoestetic range. The nano-HA technology is the differentiator — the ability to stimulate the skin's own HA production is what separates it from standard serums.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>I have fillers every eight months with Dr. Bangalee. Since I started using HA Densimatrix daily he commented that my skin quality between treatments has improved significantly. I needed less filler at my last appointment and the results lasted longer.</td><td>This serum genuinely makes a difference I can see. After two weeks my skin looked plumper — not in a puffed way, just more like it did when I was younger. My husband noticed without me saying anything which is the real test.</td><td>I'd never spent this much on a serum before. I was doubtful but the science convinced me to try it properly for three months. Month three is when the real improvement showed — deeper lines actually looked softer. I'm a convert.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>What is the difference between HA Densimatrix and other hyaluronic acid serums?</td><td>Most HA serums contain a single molecular weight — usually high molecular weight HA, which sits on the surface and provides temporary plumping. HA Densimatrix uses three distinct molecular weights engineered to act at the surface, mid-layer and deep dermis simultaneously. The nano-HA fraction stimulates the skin's own HA production — a fundamentally different mechanism to surface-level hydration that compounds over months of use.</td></tr><tr><td>Can it replace dermal filler treatments?</td><td>No — dermal fillers provide instant structural volume correction at the tissue level that a topical serum cannot replicate. However, HA Densimatrix is an excellent complement — it extends filler results, improves overall skin quality between appointments and reduces the volume of filler required over time. Many of Dr. Bangalee's patients use both as part of a coordinated anti-ageing strategy.</td></tr><tr><td>Can I use it with retinol or retinoids?</td><td>Yes — apply HA Densimatrix first on clean, dry skin, allow it to absorb, then apply your retinol product over it. The hyaluronic acid base provides a hydrating buffer that reduces the dryness and sensitivity often associated with retinoid use, making the combination more comfortable and sustainable for long-term daily use.</td></tr><tr><td>How long before I see visible results?</td><td>Surface plumping from high molecular weight HA is noticeable within days of first use. Improvements in fine lines and firmness become visible over 4–8 weeks of consistent daily use. The deep dermis restructuring effect from nano-HA builds progressively over 3–4 months — the improvement timeline mirrors in-clinic skin booster results at a pace appropriate for a daily home-care product.</td></tr><tr><td>Is it suitable for oily or acne-prone skin?</td><td>Yes — hyaluronic acid is non-comedogenic and appropriate for all skin types. The serum texture absorbs without residue. Oily skin types can use HA Densimatrix as their primary hydrating serum without adding a rich moisturiser on top, making it a valuable anti-ageing step even for those who prefer minimal layering.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-ha-densimatrix';


-- ── 14. AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream ────────────────
update public.products set description = $desc$<h3>Is Mesoestetic AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream right for you?</h3><ul><li>You have <strong>dark under-eye circles</strong> — regardless of how much sleep you get</li><li>You wake up with <strong>puffiness or eye bags</strong> that take hours to reduce</li><li>You are seeing <strong>crow's feet or fine lines</strong> forming around the eyes and want to address them before they deepen</li><li>You have been using your regular face serum around the eyes and it isn't delivering results — because it wasn't formulated for this area</li><li>You want a daily eye treatment that addresses all three concerns simultaneously rather than cycling between products</li></ul><h3>How Mesoestetic AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream works — the science</h3><p>The periocular zone — the skin around the eyes — presents a unique clinical challenge. It is <strong>3–5 times thinner</strong> than facial skin, lacks oil glands, has a different lymphatic drainage pattern, and experiences constant mechanical stress from blinking (10,000–15,000 times per day). Dark circles, puffiness and fine lines are not variations of the same problem — they are three distinct conditions requiring three distinct mechanisms of action.</p><p><strong>Dark circles</strong> have two primary causes: melanin pigmentation (brownish shadows from UV-triggered melanin deposition, similar to facial hyperpigmentation) and vascular pooling (bluish-purple shadows from blood pooling in the thin-walled capillaries beneath thin periocular skin). <strong>Vitamin C</strong> and <strong>Niacinamide</strong> address the pigmentation component; the <strong>peptide complex</strong> strengthens capillary walls to reduce the translucency that makes vascular pooling visible. <strong>Puffiness</strong> results from impaired lymphatic drainage — fluid that accumulates overnight in the loose periocular tissue. <strong>Caffeine</strong> is the most clinically established ingredient for this mechanism — it constricts blood vessels, reduces capillary permeability and stimulates lymphatic drainage, physically mobilising the fluid. For <strong>fine lines and crow's feet</strong>, the peptide complex stimulates collagen and elastin synthesis in the thin periocular skin — directly addressing the structural deficit that allows lines to form and deepen. <strong>Hyaluronic acid</strong> provides targeted hydration that immediately plumps and softens the hollow, crepey appearance of the under-eye area.</p><h3>What you will notice — and when</h3><p><strong>Within days:</strong> Visible reduction in morning puffiness and eye bags — the caffeine drainage effect is noticeable from early use. Skin around the eye feels more hydrated and comfortable. <strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Dark circles begin to brighten — the melanin pigmentation component fades progressively. The bluish vascular shadows improve more slowly as capillary wall strengthening develops. <strong>Month 2:</strong> Fine lines around the eye appear visibly softer. The periocular area has a more rested, younger quality overall. <strong>Month 3+:</strong> Progressive collagen thickening from the peptide complex — skin is genuinely more resilient and lines continue to improve with consistent use.</p><h3>How to use Mesoestetic AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream</h3><ol><li>Apply a small, pea-sized amount to the clean, dry eye contour area morning and evening</li><li>Apply using the <strong>ring finger</strong> — it exerts the least pressure; do not pull or rub the delicate periocular skin</li><li>Tap gently from the outer corner inward along the lower orbital bone and across the upper orbital bone</li><li>Allow to absorb fully before applying further products — do not apply other products directly over it immediately</li><li>In the morning, follow with <strong>Mesoprotech Melan 130+ SPF50+</strong> — the thin periocular skin is highly susceptible to UV-triggered pigmentation and photo-ageing</li></ol><h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3><table><tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr><tr><td>Peptide Complex</td><td>Stimulates collagen and elastin synthesis in thin periocular skin — addresses fine lines and crow's feet; strengthens capillary walls to reduce vascular dark circles</td></tr><tr><td>Vitamin C</td><td>Brightens melanin-pigmented dark circles; provides antioxidant protection against UV-triggered pigmentation in the periocular zone</td></tr><tr><td>Niacinamide</td><td>Inhibits melanin transfer — fades the pigmentation component of dark circles and calms the vascular redness that contributes to their appearance</td></tr><tr><td>Caffeine</td><td>Stimulates lymphatic drainage, constricts blood vessels and reduces capillary permeability — directly reduces morning puffiness and eye bags</td></tr><tr><td>Hyaluronic Acid</td><td>Targeted hydration for the hollow, crepey under-eye area — immediately plumps fine lines and restores a full, rested appearance</td></tr></table><h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3><table><tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>The eye area is where I most commonly see the gap between what patients spend and what they get. They use an excellent face serum around their eyes because it seems logical — but the periocular zone has completely different needs. The skin is thinner, the drainage mechanisms are different, the concerns are different. AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream is formulated specifically for this zone with the correct actives at the correct concentrations for periocular skin. The caffeine for drainage, the peptide complex for structural support, Vitamin C for pigmented circles — these are the three mechanisms that matter. I recommend it to virtually every anti-ageing patient who comes through my clinic, because the eye area tells the story of skin ageing faster than anywhere else on the face.</td></tr></table><h3>What our patients say</h3><table><tr><td>The puffiness reduction was the first thing I noticed — within a week my eyes looked so much less swollen in the morning. Two months later the dark circles are genuinely lighter. I look like I've had eight hours of sleep even when I haven't.</td><td>I've been using eye creams for fifteen years and this is the first one where I can point to a specific visible improvement and say that is the cream doing that. The crow's feet at the corner of my eyes are measurably softer. Dr. Bangalee recommended it and he was right.</td><td>As a man, I was sceptical about buying an eye cream. But the dark circles were starting to affect how I looked at work. Six weeks in and colleagues have commented that I look less tired. That's the result I wanted and that's what I got.</td></tr></table><h3>Frequently asked questions</h3><table><tr><td>Will it irritate sensitive eyes or bother contact lens wearers?</td><td>The eye cream is formulated for the periocular (around the eye) area and should not be applied inside the eye or directly on the lash line. Applied correctly to the orbital bone area, it is well-tolerated by most patients. Contact lens wearers should apply it before inserting lenses and ensure full absorption. If any stinging occurs, apply slightly further from the eye margin.</td></tr><tr><td>How long before dark circles visibly improve?</td><td>Dark circles have two components that respond at different rates. The melanin pigmentation component (brownish shadows) begins to improve within 2–4 weeks. The vascular component (bluish-purple shadows) improves more gradually as capillary walls strengthen — typically 6–8 weeks. Puffiness reduction from the caffeine drainage effect is noticeable from early use. Significant overall improvement across all three components is typically visible at 8–12 weeks.</td></tr><tr><td>Should I apply it right up to the lash line?</td><td>Apply to the orbital bone — the bony rim surrounding the eye socket — rather than the mobile eyelid or lash line. As the cream absorbs, it will naturally migrate to the eye contour. Applying directly to the eyelid or lash line increases the risk of product migrating into the eye and causing irritation.</td></tr><tr><td>Is there any benefit to using a dedicated eye cream if I'm already using a good anti-ageing face serum?</td><td>Yes. The eye contour has characteristics that a general face serum is not optimised for: 3–5 times thinner skin, different lymphatic drainage, no oil glands, and specific concerns (puffiness from fluid, vascular dark circles) requiring targeted actives like caffeine and specific peptide concentrations. A dedicated eye cream outperforms applying a face serum to the periocular area.</td></tr><tr><td>Can men use AGE Element Brightening Eye Cream?</td><td>Yes — dark circles, puffiness and crow's feet affect men as much as women, and the cream is equally effective regardless of gender. The formula absorbs without any visible finish, making it straightforward to incorporate into any routine. Many of Dr. Bangalee's male patients use it as part of a minimal but high-impact anti-ageing routine alongside Aox Ferulic and SPF.</td></tr></table>$desc$ where slug = 'mesoestetic-age-element-brightening-eye-cream';


-- ── Verify ────────────────────────────────────────────────
select p.name,
  length(p.description) as desc_chars,
  case when p.description ilike '%Dr. Bangalee%' then 'HAS DR B' else 'MISSING' end as dr_bangalee,
  case when p.description ilike '%patients say%' then 'HAS TESTIMONIALS' else 'MISSING' end as testimonials,
  case when p.description ilike '%asked questions%' then 'HAS FAQ' else 'MISSING' end as faq,
  case when length(p.description) > 3000 then 'OK' else 'SHORT' end as length_check
from public.products p
where p.brand_slug = 'mesoestetic'
order by p.name;
